<!--
Copilot Specification.
Piano_p1.html Specification – Layout and Functionalities

Layout Overview (ASCII representation):
+-------------------+---------+---------+
|                   |   R2A   |   R2B   |
|       R1          |  Text   | Analysis|
|                   +---------+---------+
|                   |                 R3|
|                   |    Chord List    |
+-------------------+-------------------+

Detailed Breakdown:

1. R1 – Piano Chords (Left Frame):
   - Displays chords or text data received from R2A.
   - Allows manual chord entry.
   - Components include:
      - Text Input for chords.
      - "OK" Button to send chord data to R3.
      - "Reset" Button to clear inputs and data in R1.
      - Helptext for chord formatting instructions (e.g., uppercase letters, space-separated).

2. R2A – Text Input Frame:
   - Multi-line text field for chord notations (odd rows) and plain text (even rows).
   - Validates chords in odd rows and sends them to R1.
   - Components:
      - Text Area for input.
      - "Load" Button to validate and load chords into R1.
      - "Reset" Button to clear text input.

3. R2B – Chord Analysis Frame:
   - Analyzes selected chords, displays analysis results and visualizes notes on a virtual piano (C4 to B5, 2 octaves).
   - Displays chord type (e.g., triad, tetrad, inversions, etc.) with alternates.
   - Components:
      - Visual 2-octave Piano Keyboard.
      - Text Analysis Section for note list, description, and alternative chords.

4. R3 – Chord List Panel:
   - Displays chords from R1 as rows, left to right.
   - Components:
      - Horizontal list of chord buttons for analysis (Triad, Tetrad, Inversions).
      - Option: One-octave piano visualization of chords in R3.
   - Workflow:
      - Clicking a chord button (e.g., "Triad") sends data to R2B for analysis & visualization.
      - Updates to R1 (add/remove chords) sync dynamically.

General Notes:
- CSS Grid organizes R1, R2A, R2B, R3 into a responsive layout.
- Dynamic interactivity between R1, R2A, R2B, and R3 via JavaScript.
- Panels are responsive and designed for future enhancements.
-->